\begin_layout Standard
Diffraction and interference are phenomena that happen when waves interact.
 There's not a clear distinction between the two, but---for our purposes---inter
ference is the effect arising from point sources (small wave sources --
 like the single oscillating charges in lecture), and diffraction is the
 effect from large sources.
 What's the cutoff between the two? You'll find out!
