\begin_layout Standard
The two sources shown in the figure are in phase and 
\begin_inset Formula $2.5\lambda$
\end_inset

 apart.
 Determine if there is constructive interference, destructive interference,
 or neither at points A, B, and C.
 Show your work.
 You may want to use a calculator for at least one of them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 3in
\end_inset


\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
At point A, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|d_{0}-d_{1}\right|=0$
\end_inset

 (since 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{0}=d_{1}=\lambda\sqrt{400^{2}+1.25^{2}}$
\end_inset

) so we have constructive interference.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
At point B, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|d_{0}-d_{1}\right|=2.5\lambda$
\end_inset

 so we have destructive interference (since 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{0}=\left(300-1.25\right)\lambda$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{1}=\left(300+1.25\right)\lambda$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
At point C, 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{0}=\lambda\sqrt{400^{2}+(300-1.25)^{2}}=499.25\lambda$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{1}=\lambda\sqrt{400^{2}+(300+1.25)^{2}}=500.75\lambda$
\end_inset

.
 So 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|d_{0}-d_{1}\right|=1.5\lambda$
\end_inset

 and we have destructive interference.
 Another way to answer this (without a calculator) is to recall that in
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $d\gg W$
\end_inset

 limit, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|d_{1}-d_{0}\right|=W\sin\left(\theta\right)=\lambda\frac{5}{2}\frac{3}{5}=\frac{3}{2}\lambda$
\end_inset

.
 You know 
\begin_inset Formula $\sin\left(\theta\right)=\frac{3}{5}$
\end_inset

 since it's a 3-4-5 triangle.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

